Hi Rafaella,
I can give you a more comprehensive update on Friday. But for now =E2=80=93=
 I can briefly respond as below:
Your Claims manager will update you on the content=E2=80=99s aspect of your=
 claim. I have no knowledge or jurisdiction on the contents claim. However,=
 I will follow up with your claims manager for that contents side of things=
 on Friday when I=E2=80=99m back in the office.

Re =E2=80=93 your own assessment =E2=80=93 you are welcome to book that in =
very soon. I would recommend that we meet again at your home early next wee=
k before you do that. It would be very beneficial to meet onsite again and =
have a face-to-face update on the claim=E2=80=99s progression.
As you know we have inspected the exterior wall cavities and have found som=
e smoke contamination in some isolated areas =E2=80=93 so we will explore t=
hat further to ensure that it is included in the scope of work.

I=E2=80=99m travelling all day tomorrow =E2=80=93 but will endeavor to prov=
ide you with a more comprehensive update on Friday.
Please let me know if you would like to book a site meeting in for next wee=
k.
Regards,
Grant.

[cid:image001.png@01DC176E.D8C060C0]
Grant Metson
Regional Manager - House Assessing
Phone 021 744 288
Level 5, 136 Fanshawe Street,
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142

