From: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com>
Sent: Wednesday, August 27, 2025 1:58 PM
To: Grant Metson <Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>
Subject: Re: 23 Mays Road - progression of claims response. C90306048

Hi Grant, Could you please provide me with an update against the plan: what=
 has been assessed, what still needs to be assessed (e.=E2=80=8Ag.=E2=80=8A=
, roof and gas housing), and findings so far? Also, could you please let me=
 know when I would be able to do an


Hi Grant,

Could you please provide me with an update against the plan: what has been =
assessed, what still needs to be assessed (e.g., roof and gas housing), and=
 findings so far?

Also, could you please let me know when I would be able to do an independen=
t assessment? I need to plan this.

Additionally, could you please send me an update on the contents assessment=
? I have not received any updates on the list of items, their replacement v=
alue, and I can see a number of things have not been considered yet (e.g., =
things in the cupboard at the side of the entrance of the garage, the items=
 under the deck and stairs, the items outside/beside the house).

Best regards,

Raffaella


On 29 Jul 2025, at 3:40=E2=80=AFPM, Grant Metson <Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz<=
mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>> wrote:

Hello Rafaella,
Allow me to respond with answers to your enquiries as below:

Asset Restore will be responsible for removing the gib-linings and clearing=
 the property of ant damaged items such as skirting boards, doors, panels, =
etc. This will allow us to attend the property when it is clear and clean a=
nd complete our structural assessment of the property.
The structural assessment will be undertaken by Tower Assessors [Chris or G=
rant] in conjunction with ASURNZ - Towers Technical Building Consultants. T=
his inspection will produce a technical report which will form the basis of=
 the =E2=80=98scope of works=E2=80=99. This is the correct process to deter=
mine the repairs which are required to the property. The scope of works wil=
l be shared with you, and we can review it onsite on a line-by-line basis t=
o ensure that you are satisfied that it covers all the claim related repair=
s that are necessary.


  *   A current status update on the structural assessment and any scoping =
completed to date; As explained above this will occur as soon as Asset Rest=
ore have completed the cleaning and stripping out of the property. No scopi=
ng for repairs has been completed to date. This is the next phase of the cl=
aim progression.



  *   A proposed timeline for the next phases: removal, scoping, approvals,=
 tendering, and repair; Estimates on start dates for the following claim pr=
ogression phases:

Removal of gib linings and other elements to allow structural appraisal and=
 scoping =E2=80=93 completed by Friday August 8.

Structural Assessment and draft scope of works document =E2=80=93 Completed=
 by Friday August 15.

Final scope of works shared with customer for sign-off =E2=80=93 Completed =
by Friday August 22.

Tendering process to follow scope -of-works approval =E2=80=93 2 weeks

Repair works able to commence Mid-September

  *   Confirmation of the parties responsible for each stage and how update=
s will be communicated.
Asset Restore =E2=80=93 Clean-up & strip-out. All communications documented=
 in writing.
ASURNZ =E2=80=93 Structural assessment and producing scope of works. Report=
s and scope provided in writing.
Tower Insurance - Tendering process =E2=80=93 all documents shared with cus=
tomer and provided in writing.


My mandate is strictly around structural assessing and the repairs required=
 to your house.
I will ask the Claims Manager for your contents claim to respond to your co=
ncerns with the laptop and phones.
I will ask the Motor Claims Manager to respond to your concerns with the EV=
 vehicle.

Thank you very much,
Regards,
Grant.


