</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"mso-line-height-alt:.75pt"><span style=3D"f=
ont-size:1.0pt;color:white"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
</div>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Hi Grant,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Could you please provide me with an updat=
e against the plan: what has been assessed, what still needs to be assessed=
 (e.g., roof and gas housing), and findings so far?<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Also, could you please let me know when I=
 would be able to do an independent assessment? I need to plan this.<o:p></=
o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Additionally, could you please send me an=
 update on the contents assessment? I have not received any updates on the =
list of items, their replacement value, and I can see a number of things ha=
ve not been considered yet (e.g.,
 things in the cupboard at the side of the entrance of the garage, the item=
s under the deck and stairs, the items outside/beside the house).<o:p></o:p=
></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Best regards,<o:p></o:p></p>
<p style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap">Raffaella<o:p></o:p></p>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><br>
<br>
<o:p></o:p></p>
<blockquote style=3D"margin-top:5.0pt;margin-bottom:5.0pt">
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">On 29 Jul 2025, at 3:40<span style=3D"font-family:&q=
uot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif">=E2=80=AF</span>PM, Grant Metson &lt;<a href=3D=
"mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz">Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz</a>&gt; wrote:<o=
:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hello Rafaella,</sp=
an><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Allow me to respond=
 with answers to your enquiries as below:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Asset Restore will =
be responsible for removing the gib-linings and clearing the property of an=
t damaged items such as skirting boards, doors, panels, etc. This will allo=
w us to attend the property when it
 is clear and clean and complete our structural assessment of the property.=
</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">The structural asse=
ssment will be undertaken by Tower Assessors [Chris or Grant] in conjunctio=
n with ASURNZ - Towers Technical Building Consultants. This inspection will=
 produce a technical report which will
 form the basis of the =E2=80=98scope of works=E2=80=99. This is the correc=
t process to determine the repairs which are required to the property. The =
scope of works will be shared with you, and we can review it onsite on a li=
ne-by-line basis to ensure that you are satisfied
 that it covers all the claim related repairs that are necessary.<span clas=
s=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span></span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"color:#0070C0;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-=
margin-bottom-alt:auto;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo1">
<span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif=
;color:windowtext">A current status update on the structural assessment and=
 any scoping completed to date;<span class=3D"apple-converted-space">&nbsp;=
</span></span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&q=
uot;,sans-serif">As
 explained above this will occur as soon as Asset Restore have completed th=
e cleaning and stripping out of the property. No scoping for repairs has be=
en completed to date. This is the next phase of the claim progression.</spa=
n><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-ser=
if"><o:p></o:p></span></li></ul>
<p style=3D"margin-left:.25in"><span style=3D"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&=
quot;Helvetica&quot;,sans-serif">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<ul type=3D"disc">
