=3D"mailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz">Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz</a>&gt; wrote=
:<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Good afternoon Rafa=
ella,</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I wanted to take th=
e time to thank you very much for meeting with Chris, David and myself at y=
our place this afternoon. It was much appreciated.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I felt that the mee=
ting was very productive and positive as we all discussed the next steps an=
d have agreed on the claim=E2=80=99s progression process moving forward.</s=
pan><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I would like to re-=
confirm the next steps we agreed to in writing, and share with all as below=
:</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0in;ms=
o-list:l1 level1 lfo5">
<span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Asset Restore to attend site as soon as po=
ssible and complete the process of assessing and cataloging the contents fo=
r the response of the contents claim. After assessment the contents which a=
re categorised as a total loss will
 be removed from site.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph"=
 style=3D"margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5">
<span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Asset Restore to strip out the property of=
 any fire or smoke damaged linings or other non-structural items. This will=
 enable a clear and clean structural assessment to be undertaken, from whic=
h we will produce a scope of works
 for the repairs required.</span><o:p></o:p></li><li class=3D"MsoListParagr=
aph" style=3D"margin-top:0in;margin-bottom:0in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo5">
<span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Once we have a scope of works completed =
=E2=80=93 we will share this with you to approve before we submit to our re=
pair panel for tendering.</span><o:p></o:p></li></ol>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Confirming that you=
 have notified us of the access code to be 1106.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">We will keep you up=
dated on the above process and communicate with you as we move through the =
above steps.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
/o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have spoken with =
both our Motor and our Claims Team Leaders, and they have said that the ite=
ms you have enquired about are very unlikely to be affected by the fire giv=
en their location with respect to the
 proximity of the fire. I do understand that you would like to be 100% cert=
ain that the lithium batteries in these items have not been affected from t=
he fire. The standard process in this situation is that you can undertake a=
ny testing of any of your items
 which you wish to, to obtain test results or a report which your insurer c=
an consider for inclusion in your claims. If the test results prove any dam=
age or loss to these items from the fire =E2=80=93 then your insurer will c=
onsider them within your claim.</span><o:p></o:p></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">&nbsp;</span><o:p><=
